== Tortilla Chips ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut each @Plain Taco Tortillas{6} into 8 triangles (use #scissors{} if easier).

Place on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle with @oil{}. Use two 
baking trays if necessary. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them to make sure they colour evenly.

Bake on the middle shelf of the oven until lightly golden brown and crisp, 
~{5-7%minutes}.

== Beef Filling ==

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}. Fry until the mince has 
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked 
> when no longer pink in the middle.

== Preparation ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a 
#garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

== Sauce ==

Once the mince has browned, add the garlic and @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} 
and fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, 
@Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water{75%milliliter} for the sauce.

Bring to a boil, then add the black beans. Lower the heat and simmer until the 
mixture has thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%grams} until melted.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it 
looks a little thick.

== To Serve ==

Share the Mexican spiced beef and bean mixture between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the cheese and top with a dollop of @Soured Cream{75%grams} to 
finish.

Serve the nachos alongside for dipping. Enjoy!